osA7) and third-generation cephalosporin (blaCMY-2) resistance as well as the Salmonella-speciﬁc invA gene and the universal 16S rRNA genes. The PCR assay was speciﬁc and sensitive for blaCMY-2 and fosA7 harboring Salmonella Heidelberg. However, some other Salmonella serovars containing these two resistance genes could also be detected by the developed PCR method.},
